:::summary
General Conference is a twice-yearly worldwide gathering of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in which the President of the Church, members of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles, and other General Authorities deliver inspired messages of doctrine, counsel, and testimony to members across the globe. Held each April and October in Salt Lake City, Utah, General Conference is considered by Latter-day Saints to be a living manifestation of the Restoration — evidence that God continues to speak to His people through living prophets and apostles just as He did in ancient times.
:::

